President Obama has announced the nomination of Dr. Jim Yong Kim to be President of the World Bank. Dr. Kim has dedicated his career to improving the lives of people in developing countries and advocating for global health. He has served as the President of Dartmouth College since 2009 and has launched initiatives to improve healthcare delivery and combat HIV/AIDS. Dr. Kim's work in global health has earned him recognition and awards, including a MacArthur "Genius" Fellowship. He has published extensively and holds degrees from Brown University, Harvard Medical School, and Harvard University.